<p itemprop="description">A user researcher plans, conducts, and analyses user research to inform design and product decisions. They understand user needs and behaviours, apply appropriate research methodologies, and communicate insights effectively to multidisciplinary teams to ensure services meet user needs.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Plan and conduct comprehensive user research using appropriate methodologies</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Design research studies including interviews, usability testing, and field research</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Analyse research data and synthesise findings into actionable insights</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Communicate research findings through reports, presentations, and workshops</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Collaborate with designers, product managers, and developers on research integration</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Ensure research practices meet ethical standards and accessibility requirements</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Build research repositories and contribute to organisational research knowledge</li>
    </ul>
</section>

